snippet.textDisplay:
My thoughts about the MV.

Lia is a royalty and the doll she's holding was her. Notice how she was turning the key-thing at first but when it came off she realized that no one can control her now. That is also why at first she's so careful on walking above the table because she needs to perfect and all but after that she went crazy and just never cared about the things that came on her way.

Yeji is at a party..probably at a disco or a bar. Yeji was uncomfortable at first. People were dancing but Yeji wasn't. Why? Because she is wary of her actions. She doesn't want to dance because people might judge her or something like that. She's just observing how the people dance but laterrr she jived with the music and danced her heart out.

Chaeryeong. She is a typical school girl who goes to school to study. Everything was fine until drones came and observe what she was doing. I think Chaeryeong was bugged by the drones it kept observing and chasing her. Those drones may be the people telling her things that she has to do and has to be. She ran but in the end after realizing, she confronted the drones that she can be herself and not what they wanted her to be.

Yuna on the other hand is a runway model. She's backstage waiting for her turn to ramp but after all those waiting, she grew tired of her heels and wanted it out of her feet but she's worried if people will see her taking it off. That is why she was looking around. After waiting her time on the runway came. She went inside barefooted wearing a yellow dress. She went inside without thinking about what will people tell about her. She even mocked them by staring at their camera, dancing and taking selfies.

Ryujin. I think Ryujin was the KPop idol. She went to the toilet holding a scissor and was just staring at the camera. There was once a short interview of Ryujin telling she likes herself more in a short hair. The Ryujin in the MV was Ryujin herself. Being a KPOP Idol, fans and haters sometimes get so obssesed of how idols look like by telling them how they should look like. That is why in the MV, Ryujin showed that she can shorten her hair if she likes. Because that's what she is. And she likes being herself.

The MV is simply telling us to stop pretending as someone we are not. Each one of us is unique and we must show it to the world.

These girls are very empowering especially to young girls like me because of their song. MORE POWERS ITZY! Truly, All is in you. #STREAMWANNABE

She doesn't want to dance because people might judge her or something like that. She's just observing how the people dance but laterrr she jived with the music and danced her heart out.

Chaeryeong. She is a typical school girl who goes to school to study. Everything was fine until drones came and observe what she was doing. I think Chaeryeong was bugged by the drones it kept observing and chasing her. Those drones may be the people telling her things that she has to do and has to be. She ran but in the end after realizing, she confronted the drones that she can be herself and not what they wanted her to be.

Yuna on the other hand is a runway model. She's backstage waiting for her turn to ramp but after all those waiting, she grew tired of her heels and wanted it out of her feet but she's worried if people will see her taking it off. That is why she was looking around. After waiting her time on the runway came. She went inside barefooted wearing a yellow dress. She went inside without thinking about what will people tell about her. She even mocked them by staring at their camera, dancing and taking selfies.

Ryujin. I think Ryujin was the KPop idol. She went to the toilet holding a scissor and was just staring at the camera. There was once  a short interview of Ryujin telling she likes herself more in a short hair. The Ryujin in the MV was Ryujin herself. Being a KPOP Idol, fans and haters sometimes get so obssesed of how idols look like by telling them how they should look like. That is why in the MV, Ryujin showed that she can shorten her hair if she likes. Because that's what she is. And she likes being herself.

The MV is simply telling us to stop pretending as someone we are not. Each one of us is unique and we must show it to the world. 

These girls are very empowering especially to young girls like me because of their song. MORE POWERS ITZY! Truly, All is in you. #STREAMWANNABE
